<font color="#FF0000">SHE EARNED HER OPPORTUNITIES..</font><br>
<tt>Sun Dec  1 13:20:30 US/Eastern 1996
</tt><p>
Unfortunately I am not surprised Maya Lin had her race used against her when there was a controversy about her design, a very cheap shot,but it doesn't stun me, it sickens me.<br><br>
I think she did a good job. I think that if you want to say, well, is she merited the &quot;fame&quot; she has gotten? Yes, damn right, she EARNED it,she earned the opportunties that have come her way. I have a life and don't lose sleep over this.<br><br>
I think Maya is a great example for girls, women of all races.She has shown strength,persistance and sensitivity as well as artistic vision.She didn't let the bastards grind her down. She is a good example of standing up for artistic expression and she had formidable opposition to deal with at a very young age.She is someone you can appreciate whether you are male or female. I don't believe in putting people on pedestals, but she certainly is worthy of respect.<br>
Maija Murphy<br>
Oh yea, she shares a great name too,even thou my name is of eastern european origin! <br>

